      "content": "okay but those \"practical\" concerns like taxes and wait times feel like distractions from the actual human cost. if a policy is more \"efficient\" but leaves millions without basic medicine, isn't that policy fundamentally wrong? isn't it kinda weird to treat fiscal efficiency as an equal weight to human survival?",
